Question: Do you think age restrictions on drinking are effective?
Answer:
I believe that age restrictions on drinking are effective, albeit the effects are unsatisfactory.  Inndividuals under legal age can still have accesses  to alcohol from multiple ways such as offering from older friends and illegal dealers. But these restrictions are effective in defferrance. At least some people will not drink under age or buy alcohols for people underage in the fear of against the law. Moreover, even if they did break the restrictions, they might be more conservative in the amount of consumption.